The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of memory subsystems, which is a topic that falls under multiple CS sub-categories. cs.AR (Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes new techniques to improve the performance of memory systems. cs.OS (Operating Systems) is also likely as the paper discusses virtual memory, which is a key component of modern operating systems. cs.ARCH (Computer Architecture) is another possible category as the paper proposes new hardware mechanisms to improve memory efficiency. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper discusses techniques that can improve the performance of distributed and parallel systems.
